 [[ancient Egypt]], through the years in the desert, and up to the entrance of the [[twelve tribes of Israel]] to the [[promised land]] of [[Canaan]] (later [[Israel]]).<ref name=\"Amaseffer Homepage - Band\">{{cite web |url= http://www.amaseffer.com/band.htm|title= Amaseffer Homepage - The Story of the Band|accessdate= 2008|publisher = Amaseffer}}</ref> The first in the trilogy, the album tells the story of the events starting with the Hebrews slavery, through the birth of [[Moses]] and ends with the [[Plagues of Egypt|ten plagues of Egypt]].<ref name=\"Holy Bible - Exodus\">{{cite web |url= http://www.online-literature.com/bible/Exodus/|title= The Holy Bible - Exodus|accessdate= |publisher= God through Moses}}</ref>\n\nIn the time of the recording, the band just parted ways with their vocalist [[Andy Kuntz]], and lead vocals on the album were recorded by [[Mats Leven]] ([[Krux]], ex-[[Therion (band)|Therion]], ex-[[At Vance]], [[Yngwie Malmsteen]]).<ref name=\"BlubberMouth - Mats Leven\">{{cite web|url= http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=77220|archive-url= https://archive.is/20130201083809/http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=77220|url-status= dead|archive-date= 2013-02-01|title= Mats Leven to Guest on Amaseffer Project|accessdate= 2007-07-20|publisher= blabbermouth.net}}</ref> Additional vocals were recorded by [[Kobi Farhi]] of [[Orphaned Land]], [[Angela Gossow]] of [[Arch Enemy]] and [[Yotam Avni]] of [[Prey for Nothing]].\n\nAlthough the album's sound mostly considered [[progressive metal]], it also contains a mixture of [[symphonic metal]], [[world music]] and Middle Eastern touches.<ref name=\"InsideOut Amaseffer\">{{cite web |url= http://www.insideout.de/catalog/product_info.php?products_id=612&osCsid=05d2aa9aade2d1684e23b042a5621c79|title= Amaseffer CD description on InsideOut Music web page|accessdate= 2008-06-06|publisher = InsideOut Music}}</ref>\n\nThe band's drummer and main songwriter [[Erez Yohanan]] has produced the album, and is also providing vocals as the narrator of the story. The album was mixed and mastered by [[Markus Teske]].\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| total_length    = \n| title1          = Sorrow\n| length1         = 2:40\n| title2          = Slaves for Life\n| length2         = 8:27\n| title3          = Birth of Deliverance\n| length3         = 11:11\n| title4          = Midian\n| length4         = 11:47\n| title5          = Zipporah\n| length5         = 6:10\n| title6          = Burning Bush\n| length6         = 6:33\n| title7          = The Wooden Staff \n| length7         = 9:13\n| title8          = Return to Egypt \n| length8         = 3:25\n| title9          = Ten Plagues\n| length9         = 11:28\n| title10         = Land of the Dead \n| length10        = 6:53\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Mats Leven]] - lead & backing vocals\n*[[Hanan Avramovich]] - guitars\n*[[Yuval Kramer]] - guitars, bass\n*[[Erez Yohanan]] - drums, percussion, narrating vocals\n*[[Kobi Farhi]] - oriental vocals\n*[[Angela Gossow]] - growled vocals on \"Midian\"\n*[[Yotam Avni]] - growled vocals on \"Midian\"\n*[[Maya Avraham]] - female vocals on \"Zipporah\"\n*[[Amir Gvirtzman]] - flute\n*[[Yair Yona]] - bass on \"Zipporah\" and \"Burning Bush\"\n*[[Yatziv Caspi]] - tablas on \"Slaves for Life\" and \"Midian\"\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2008 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Amaseffer albums]]\n[[Category:Inside Out Music albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Slaves for Life\n| type       = album\n| artist     = [[Amaseffer]]\n| cover      = Amaseffer_album.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = Israel: 6 June 2008<br> World: 24 June 2008\n| recorded   = 29 June 2007 - 14 July 2007 at Bazement Studio, Germany\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Progressive metal]]<br>[[Folk metal]]\n| length     = 1:17:51\n| label      = [[InsideOut Music]]\n| producer   = Erez Yohanan\n| prev_t